# TypeScript

**Agent:** Write arrow-only TS ‚Äî `const name = ... =>`; follow `AGENTS.md` naming, whitespace, and control flow.

## Why types

- **Agent discoverability:** Exported interfaces and type aliases form a crawlable contract graph (props, store shapes, API payloads) without inferring behavior from runtime code alone.
- **Code quality:** Strong, named types replace implicit `any` and loose objects; export types on public module boundaries.
- **Validation:** All code must pass `tsc --noEmit`; do not introduce compile errors.

## Never do

- No `.js` or `.jsx` ‚Äî use `.ts` / `.tsx` only; migrate or delete legacy JS if encountered.
- No `function` keyword ‚Äî including nested handlers in components and `useEffect`.
- No `class` ‚Äî factories return plain objects.
- No `any` ‚Äî use `unknown` and narrow when shape is uncertain.
- No comments in agent-generated code.
- No barrel `index.ts` files ‚Äî import from the concrete module path (e.g. `./registry.ts`, not `./index.ts` or the folder alone).

## Types

| Area | Rule |
|------|------|
| Object shapes | `interface`; `type` for unions/intersections |
| Props / config | Named types; export when reused across features |
| Hooks / factories | Explicit parameter and return types on exports |
| Type-only imports | `import type { ... }` |
| Tests | Runtime tests in `*.test.ts` / `*.test.tsx`; type validation = `tsc --noEmit` |

## Arrow functions

- Single expression ‚Üí one-line, no block body.
- Multi-statement block ‚Üí whitespace per `AGENTS.md` (blank line only between logical steps).

## Modules and factories

| Rule | Pattern |
|------|---------|
| `use*` prefix | React hooks in `src/features/` only ‚Äî `react.mdc` |
| Pure helpers | Verb/noun names, no `use` |
| Exports | `export const` default; `export default` for components and static config only |
| Factory guard | `if (!dep) throw new Error('dep is not defined')` at entry |
| Factory args | Destructured config + `= {}` outer fallback |

```typescript
export const createStore = ({ initialState = {} }: CreateStoreConfig = {}): Store => {

    if (!initialState) throw new Error('initialState is not defined');

    return { state: initialState };
};
```

## Idioms

| Rule | Pattern |
|------|---------|
| Optional callbacks | `onClose?.()` |
| Nullish / lazy init | `??`, `\|\|=` |
| Strings | Single quotes |
| Multiline literals | Trailing commas |
| Destructure | Rename for clarity: `{ id: userId }` |
| Chained calls | One per line, indented |

Prefer early returns ‚Äî `AGENTS.md`.
